VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT ServerCertificateValidationCallback\s*=\s*\{[^}]*\$true\}|ServerCertificateValidationCallback\s*=\s*\{\s*\$true\s*\}
WHEN EXPR MISSING:test|development|localhost|staging
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects TLS certificate validation disabled via ServerCertificateValidationCallback returning true for all certificates.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for TLS Validation Disabled via Callback.
